'''Louisiana Highway 549''' ('''LA 549''') is a [[state highway]] in [[Louisiana]] that serves [[Union Parish, LA|Union Parish]]. It spans {{convert|15.76|mi|km}}.

==Route description==
From the south, LA 549 begins at an intersection with [[Louisiana Highway 15|LA 15]], heading in a northeastern direction towards [[Strong, Arkansas|Strong, AR]]. LA 549 passes through hilly areas before meeting [[Louisiana Highway 348|LA 348]]. LA 348 travels due east towards [[Louisiana Highway 33|LA 33]], and on to [[Marion, Louisiana|Marion]]. 

Heading north, LA 549 passes the Union Wildlife Management Area before meeting [[Louisiana Highway 551|LA 551]] in the small community of [[Oakland, Louisiana|Oakland]]. Just over a mile north of this intersection, LA 549 crosses the state line into [[Arkansas]], changing to [[Arkansas Highway 275|AR 275]] and heading north to the town of [[Strong, Arkansas|Strong, AR]] and [[U.S. Route 82|US 82]].

LA 142 is an undivided, two-lane road for its entire route.

